into the form \( y^{\,\prime} + p(t) y = g(t)\) and find
\( p(t) \) and \( g(t) \).
$BR
$BR
\( p(t) = \) 
\{ ans_rule(30) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("formulas") \}
$BR
\( g(t) = \) 
\{ ans_rule(30) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("formulas") \}
$BR
$BR
